DEVICEPROTECTION REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION
=========================================

What is DeviceProtection? Well, you can find more information behind this link:

    http://upnp.org/specs/gw/deviceprotection1/

This directory contains sources for:
    - LinuxIGDv2 with UPnP DeviceProtection v.1.0 service
    - gupnp-universal-cp UPnP control point with UPnP DeviceProtection v.1.0 support
    - Other related components


BUILDING IN UBUNTU AND DEBIAN
=============================

You can build all for x86 environment with these commands:

    mkdir -p ~/linuxigd2_test/src/ && cd ~/linuxigd2_test/src/
    git clone http://git.gitorious.org/igd2-for-linux/deviceprotection.git deviceprotection
    cd ~/linuxigd2_test/src/deviceprotection/system_test/
    ./test.sh all

More detailed instructions are in Gitorious wiki:

    http://gitorious.org/igd2-for-linux/pages/DeviceProtectionInstallationGuide

